cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a framework for classifying examples with missing features using a logistic regression classifier. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using the framework for image classification (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), indicating that it may be applicable to computer vision and language tasks. Additionally, the paper uses geometric programming to learn a naive Bayes distribution, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
